aec does administer the writing skills test (wst) which may be required of all undergraduate and graduate students prior to enrollment in a 100w course.the csu requires that each campus establish a graduation writing assessment requirement (gwar) for all upper division students. at sjsu, completion of 100w course with a passing grade satisfies the gwar. however, a passing score on the wst is required of all undergraduate and graduate students prior to enrollment in 100w courses.sample test questions are available at the testing office located in the industrial studies (is) building.the peer connections center provides tutoring to prepare for the wst. to register, go topeer connectionsin student services center (ssc) 600 or call (408) 924-2587.deadlines for testing with accommodations differ from those set by thetesting office..the wst costs $38. aec students must pay for the wst before meeting with a aec counselor. payment is handled at cashiering services in the student service center (ssc); online fee payment by credit card is now available atcashnet. students must provide a copy of their receipt to the aec counselor to set up accommodations.students will receive an email aec; it will specify the location and time of the wst. all students are required to bring pens, and a dictionary for the test; other accommodations must be approved by a aec counselor. to avoid problems on the day of testing, all students must arrive on time and are expected to clarify accommodations or testing concerns with their aec counselor prior to the exam date.the7th street garage (on san salvador) and 4th street garage (on san fernando)have available parking on saturdays. the current cost for a day permit is $8.00.office emailsstaff directoryadministration building(adm)room 110accessible education centersan jos state universityone washington squaresan jose, ca 95192-0168mon: 9 am - 5 pmtues: 9 am - 5 pmwed: 10 am - 5 pmthurs: 9 am - 4 pmfri: 9 am - 4 pm